This paper deals with word-level analogical reasoning and commonsense knowledge, which are topics that are commonly studied in natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning models to embed commonsense structures, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper also involves the use of an ontology to annotate Chinese words, which could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) research.
